    <section id="about">
        <center><h2>About Kattappana</h2></center>
        <p>
            Kattappana is a picturesque town located in the Idukki district of Kerala, India. Known for its lush greenery, rolling hills, and pleasant climate, Kattappana is a popular destination for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. The town is surrounded by tea plantations, spice gardens, and waterfalls, making it a perfect getaway for those seeking tranquility.
        </p>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/93/Distant_view_of_Kattappana_town.jpg" alt="Kattappana Landscape" width="800" height="400">
    </section>

    <hr>

    <!-- Attractions Section -->
    <section id="attractions">
        <h2>Top Attractions in Kattappana</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ramakkalmedu:</strong> A scenic hilltop offering breathtaking views of the Western Ghats.</li>
            <li><strong>Idukki Arch Dam:</strong> One of the largest arch dams in Asia, located near Kattappana.</li>
            <li><strong>Tea Plantations:</strong> Explore the vast tea estates and learn about tea production.</li>
            <li><strong>Spice Gardens:</strong> Visit local spice gardens to see the cultivation of cardamom, pepper, and more.</li>
            <li><strong>Waterfalls:</strong> Discover hidden waterfalls like Keezharathur and Thommankuthu.</li>
<li> And much more....<a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=top+sights+in+kattappana&sca_esv=5d466d0b992978df&rlz=1C1VDKB_enIN1128IN1128&sxsrf=AHTn8zpjZxrAzxdJ2XBYp7Nyl3GFDrulUw%3A1740585000649&ei=KDi_Z5mxJ9SRseMPhObGiA8&oq=top+sights+in+kattapppana&gs__AQ&sclient=gws-wiz-serp"><u>More visits</u></a></li>
        </ul>
